28/11/2004
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Montenegro Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic declared Saturday (27 November) that no indictees wanted by the International Criminal Tribunal for the Former Yugoslavia (ICTY) are hiding on Montenegrin territory. In a statement for Radio Free Europe, Djukanovic said Montenegro was determined to be a "responsible partner" of the international community.
In other news, Serbia-Montenegro Foreign Minister Vuk Draskovic said during a visit to Germany Friday that Belgrade had to realise that "time was running out" for co-operation with the ICTY. He again warned that integration in the EU would not be possible without full co-operation. (Tanjug - 27/11/04; Beta - 26/11/04)
